<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-02-16T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-02-16T19:00:00-05:00" n="253" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d253">
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">No. 253</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">765.5–<gloss target="#t_MAP1">MAP</gloss>/2–1651: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Italy</gloss>
                                </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d253fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_BJO1">Bell</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_CH1">Cleveland</persName> and cleared with
                                    Peterson; sent by pouch to London for <gloss target="#t_USDep1">USDep</gloss>, Paris, and Heidelberg.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-02-16T19:00:00-05:00">February 16, 1951—7 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3623. <gloss target="#t_Tomap1">Tomap</gloss>.</p>
                            <list>
                                <label>1.</label>
                                <item>Fol is joint State–<gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss>
                                    msg.</item>
                                <label>2.</label>
                                <item>We have just recd Embdes 2263<note n="2" xml:id="d253fn2">For
                                        the text of the memorandum by the <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> Mission in Italy, which was sent to
                                        Washington as an enclosure to despatch 2263, see Document
                                        249.</note> and feel certain respects which will be apparent
                                    Mission and <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>, it not entirely
                                    consistent <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 3553,<note n="3" xml:id="d253fn3">Document 251.</note> particularly
                                    para 4 and last sentence, para 2, latter. Note especially phrase
                                    “same amt or more”.</item>
                                <label>3.</label>
                                <item>Also concerned lest Itals receive impression they will receive
                                    firm commitment econ aid for bal this fiscal year and next year
                                    before adequate assurances and evidences have been presented on
                                    adequacy Ital program from mil and production viewpoint, in
                                    accordance with criteria outlined para 5, <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 3143.<note n="4" xml:id="d253fn4">Document 246.</note> Appreciate fully
                                    difficulty reaching conclusions adequacy Ital mil program
                                    because of its present tentative state. Believe, however,
                                    important <pb facs="0615" n="573" xml:id="pg_573"/> retain US
                                    freedom of action on aid until maximum possible assurances re
                                    fullest use Ital econ resources and mounting maximum possible
                                    def production effort have been obtained.</item>
                                <label>4.</label>
                                <item>Note para I 2. language ur memo<note n="5" xml:id="d253fn5">The memorandum under reference is the enclosure to despatch
                                        2263 cited in footnote 2 above.</note> appears contemplate
                                    aid for imports only against mil expenditures which obviously
                                    inconsistent <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 3143 and
                                    presumably not intended.</item>
                                <label>5.</label>
                                <item>Re aid figures, wld appreciate ur recommendation before any
                                    final position taken as requested <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 3150 to Rome.<note n="6" xml:id="d253fn6">Not printed, but see footnote 14, Document 246.</note>
                                </item>
                            </list>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>